{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on old-compactor snapshot of new CREATE events: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fa692d14e5835e09e"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"old-compactor snapshot of new CREATE events"},{"coaching":"Plan how compiled_state schema after rollback will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["ffe3669ee5a0a1f06"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"compiled_state schema after rollback"},{"coaching":"Pin down reconciler-created placeholder identity entity type with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f68bf0382914d4a2f"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"reconciler-created placeholder identity entity type"},{"coaching":"Pin down pytest filter token inconsistency across AC levels with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f64128aa08f679d5b"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"pytest filter token inconsistency across AC levels"},{"coaching":"Pin down outbound Jira channel-preservation contract with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fde012c6939060c0f"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"outbound Jira channel-preservation contract"},{"coaching":"Plan how helper-flow channel coverage across all entity types will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fa0a1dcba740d2b94"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"helper-flow channel coverage across all entity types"},{"coaching":"Propagate the revision for unfiltered export NDJSON test coverage in children to the child tickets.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f86a40df57ea69326"],"move_id":"11","move_name":"propagate to children","subject":"unfiltered export NDJSON test coverage in children"},{"coaching":"Plan how lint validation of documentation changes in e622 will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f6f7cb780bcd99861"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"lint validation of documentation changes in e622"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":0,"dropped":9,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":9989,"file_impact":8,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":3,"edges":3,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":2514,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":4108},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":8,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["E1","E3","G3"],"floored_finding_ids":["f68bf0382914d4a2f","fde012c6939060c0f","fa0a1dcba740d2b94","f86a40df57ea69326"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":270.7,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":463990.9,"total_ms":464395.3,"verify_requests":1},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Address the first-compaction rollback gap: specify that either (a) CREATE events must not be retired until at least one new-code SNAPSHOT has been written (i.e., enforce a 'new-code-compacted first' precondition before retiring events), or (b) document this as a DATA LOSS RISK with an explicit operator notice alongside the existing rollback guidance.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'process_snapshot restores every unknown compiled_state key verbatim' — this only helps when creation_channel is already in compiled_state, not when the old compactor builds compiled_state for the first time from a CREATE event that has creation_channel in its event data.","The rollback sequence: new code writes CREATE with creation_channel → rollback before any new-code SNAPSHOT → old compactor runs first compaction → compiled_state lacks creation_channel → CREATE events retired → creation_channel permanently lost.","DATA LOSS RISK: creation_channel recorded in CREATE events can be lost if old-code compaction precedes new-code compaction during the rollback window."],"finding":"During a rollback window, if the old compactor performs the FIRST compaction of new-code CREATE events (which carry `creation_channel` in the event payload), it will build a `compiled_state` SNAPSHOT without `creation_channel`. Once those CREATE events are retired, the recorded channel value is irrecoverably lost. The plan's 'older compactor carries creation_channel forward verbatim' guarantee only applies when creation_channel is ALREADY in `compiled_state` (i.e., a new-code SNAPSHOT already exists) — it does not protect against the first-compaction gap during rollback.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa692d14e5835e09e","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback paragraph: 'The operational back-out disables or reverts new writers while retaining the reader projection…' and 'the older compactor carries creation_channel forward even though its output schema does not expose it'","norm_id":"nc5282c03b8f69696","priority":0.5025,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Operator rolls back the feature flag / binary before the first compaction cycle runs on new-code CREATE events; old compactor then compacts those events, producing a SNAPSHOT without creation_channel; CREATE events are subsequently expired; re-enabling the feature yields `unknown` instead of the originally recorded value."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add a precondition to the rollback runbook: creation-bearing CREATE events must not be retired before at least one successful new-code compaction has stored `creation_channel` in `compiled_state`. Alternatively, document the bounded loss window and add an AC that the rollback runbook states this explicitly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"medium","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"high","reversibility":"hard","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit post-rollback schema-state assertion to the Architecture Decisions or Risks section: specify what `compiled_state.creation_channel` equals for (a) tickets with an existing new-code SNAPSHOT, (b) tickets whose only compaction occurred under old code, and (c) tickets never compacted — so operators and downstream consumers have a deterministic expectation.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["The plan states rollback is 'event-log-safe' but does not enumerate the compiled_state shape after old-code compaction runs on (a) SNAPSHOTs that already have creation_channel vs. (b) raw CREATE events that have creation_channel but no SNAPSHOT yet.","T11 POST-ROLLBACK SCHEMA STATE requirement: 'the plan must assert on the schema STATE AFTER rollback, not merely that rollback exits 0'.","ABSENCE: no AC or Architecture Decision states what compiled_state.creation_channel equals after rollback recompaction."],"finding":"The plan does not assert the schema STATE of `compiled_state` after a rollback, only that the event log remains 'event-log-safe' and the public field is 'hidden'. It does not state whether `compiled_state` inside existing SNAPSHOTs retains, loses, or corrupts `creation_channel` after old-code recompaction, leaving the post-rollback invariant unspecified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffe3669ee5a0a1f06","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback paragraph: 'Full downgrade to the immediately pre-feature binary remains event-log-safe but hides the public field; notify downstream show/list/export consumers before such a downgrade.'","norm_id":"n89b01ab14e2a9e83","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An auditor or automated consumer queries creation_channel after a rollback recompaction and receives inconsistent values — unknown for some tickets (first-compaction gap), the original recorded value for others (pre-existing SNAPSHOT), with no documented explanation of which tickets will fall into which bucket."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"Parent AC2's proof command uses `-k inbound_recorded` (a single camelCase/underscore token that pytest matches as a substring), but child e622 AC1 uses `-k \"inbound and recorded\"` (a pytest boolean AND expression selecting tests containing BOTH 'inbound' AND 'recorded'). These two filter expressions select different test node sets: `-k inbound_recorded` matches tests whose node IDs contain the literal string 'inbound_recorded', while `-k \"inbound and recorded\"` matches tests containing 'inbound' AND separately 'recorded' anywhere. A test named 'test_inbound_new_issue_recorded' would be caught by the AND filter but not by the underscore literal. The parent completion verifier will run the parent AC command, which may miss tests the child designed to satisfy its criterion.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f64128aa08f679d5b","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74, parent AC2","norm_id":"nf03d63cb34f388ba","priority":0.33,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Update parent AC2 prove command to use '-k \"inbound and recorded\"' to match e622 AC1, OR update e622 AC1 and its test function names to use the underscore-concatenated form 'inbound_recorded' to match the parent.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify how LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID are shared between `rebar.reducer._version` and `inbound_translate._event_meta` given reconciler spec-loading isolation — either document an allowed import direction, use a third-party re-export, or explicitly note that the constants are duplicated with a drift-detection contract test.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["inbound_translate.py lines 166-167 already use inline string literals `_rebar_env('ENV_ID', 'reconciler')` / `_rebar_env('AUTHOR', 'reconciler')` — a direct import from rebar.reducer is not currently present","tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_env_aliasing.py confirms reconciler modules are spec-loaded in isolation: 'reconciler modules are spec-loaded under test where a cross-module import of a shared shim would not resolve' (inbound_translate.py line 47-48)","Plan states 'inbound_translate._event_meta uses them as its defaults; the reducer imports the same symbols' without specifying import direction or isolation workaround"],"finding":"The plan requires `inbound_translate._event_meta` to import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID from `rebar.reducer._version` to use them as its default author/env values, but reconciler modules (including `inbound_translate.py`) are spec-loaded under test in an isolated namespace where a cross-package import from `rebar.reducer._version` may not resolve. The plan does not acknowledge this constraint or specify how the import should be structured.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fad4a6db28c9c67bc","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'inbound_translate._event_meta uses them as its defaults; the reducer imports the same symbols' / e622 Files section: 'src/rebar/reducer/_version.py and src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py: shared exact legacy Jira constants'","norm_id":"nfaa45579f9ffe955","priority":0.3015,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Story e622 implementer adds `from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID` to inbound_translate.py; tests that spec-load the module fail to resolve the import and the test suite breaks.","Alternatively the constants are duplicated (not shared), defeating the single-source-of-truth goal and allowing the inference predicate to silently diverge from the producer defaults."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"insufficient","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"insufficient","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add 'make lint' (or equivalent documentation lint) to e622-a596-3ceb-4f74's acceptance criteria so documentation changes are validated at e622's own review boundary.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3","G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["e622 file_impact lists: docs/event-schema.md, docs/cli-reference.md, docs/output-schemas.md","e622 verify_commands: DD-X1 (test_creation_channel.py), DD-X2 (io tests), DD-X3 (inbound_leaf_bodies) — none include make lint","568c AC7: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint' — first lint check after e622 lands","Parent AC11: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint'","6fe2 verify_commands include DD-L4: 'make lint'; 568c includes make lint in AC7; e622 has neither","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 modifies three documentation files (docs/event-schema.md, docs/cli-reference.md, docs/output-schemas.md) that the parent AC11 validates with 'make lint', but e622's own acceptance criteria and verify_commands include no lint step. Documentation lint failures introduced by e622 are deferred to child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87, which runs 'make lint' only after its own SNAPSHOT documentation changes.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6f7cb780bcd99861","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74, Acceptance Criteria and verify_commands; parent AC11","norm_id":"nfa75d4986762c8ff","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A documentation change in e622 introduces a broken markdown link or violates a lint rule in docs/cli-reference.md; this is invisible until 568c's review, forcing a retroactive fix to the already-reviewed e622 story on the feature branch.","The Gerrit feature branch gated merge runs the parent completion verifier which includes make lint; the failure traces back to e622's documentation changes, requiring an out-of-sequence amendment."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a final e622 AC: 'Documentation changes pass lint. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint.' Align with 6fe2's DD-L4 pattern.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"insufficient","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Enumerate the concrete modules/call sites for every CREATE-backed helper flow (ideas, identities, session logs) in the plan body so an executor does not have to discover them; list each alongside its owning entry boundary (create_core vs. direct writer).","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'All CREATE-backed helper flows, including ideas, identities, and session logs, attributed to the interface that invoked them.'","'Missed producer path: enumerate every create_core and direct CREATE writer call site and pin each public facade/helper with a behavioral test.'","The plan identifies two creation seams (composer.py:create_core and apply_inbound_records.py) but does not list which helpers (ideas, identities, session logs) flow through which seam."],"finding":"The plan's IN scope includes 'All CREATE-backed helper flows, including ideas, identities, and session logs' but never enumerates the concrete call sites or modules involved. The risk mitigation delegates enumeration to the executor ('enumerate every create_core and direct CREATE writer call site'), leaving the full set of affected paths as a discovery task rather than a stated decision.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe72945b0384e4faf","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope (IN) / Risks and Mitigations — 'Missed producer path'","norm_id":"n50f77d7e5d623dbd","priority":0.1237,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An executing agent completes CLI/MCP/Python channel attribution for standard tickets but misses a session-log helper that calls create_core through an intermediate layer, leaving it with an incorrect or unknown channel value and no failing test to catch it."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a table or bullet list under Architecture Decisions or Scope identifying each helper (e.g. `_commands/ideas.py`, `_commands/identities.py`, session-log writer) and stating which entry boundary (create_core / apply_inbound_records / direct) it routes through, so the channel-declaration point is unambiguous without codebase investigation.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify a concrete back-out mechanism for schema/typed-surface consumers on full binary downgrade (e.g., keep creation_channel in the schema as optional with a sentinel fallback, document a versioned schema pin, or define an expand-contract sequence) rather than relying solely on downstream notification.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'notify downstream show/list/export consumers before such a downgrade' — notification is acknowledgement, not a rollback mechanism","T4 criterion: 'The remedy is an explicit rollback/back-out plan or expand-contract — acknowledgement alone is insufficient'","The plan adds creation_channel to public schema (ticket_state.schema.json) and generated types; on full downgrade those schema artifacts revert, breaking any consumer already depending on the field"],"finding":"The full-binary-downgrade back-out path for schema and typed-surface consumers relies solely on 'notify downstream show/list/export consumers' without specifying a concrete rollback mechanism (e.g., schema version pin, expand-contract sequence, or versioned API surface). Consumers that have adopted `creation_channel` from the published schema would silently lose the field on downgrade, and the plan provides no actionable remedy beyond notification.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe24d394bc24043e5","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback paragraph: 'Full downgrade to the immediately pre-feature binary remains event-log-safe but hides the public field; notify downstream show/list/export consumers before such a downgrade.'","norm_id":"n1c7b50882b3a93b7","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An audit pipeline starts filtering on creation_channel; a full binary rollback removes the field from schema outputs without a versioned fallback, silently breaking the pipeline.","A downstream exporter validates exported NDJSON against the new schema; rollback strips the field and causes validation failures with no migration path."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add an explicit expand-contract step: publish the schema change first with creation_channel as optional/nullable and a documented unknown sentinel, then enable writers. On rollback, the schema remains valid (field is optional), writers are disabled, and readers return unknown — no consumer breakage. Document this as the rollback contract in the Architecture Decisions section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Capture the three-signal inference rationale, the inference-marker-present-only-when-true encoding rule, and the compaction/SNAPSHOT preservation contract in a persistent artifact (ADR, CLAUDE.md section, or docs/architecture/creation-channel.md) so the decisions survive ticket closure.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan states docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md will be updated, but these are schema-reference docs, not decision records.","The three-signal predicate rationale, the 'marker present only when true' encoding decision, and the 'process_snapshot restores unknown compiled_state keys verbatim' compaction contract are explained only in the ticket body, which is ephemeral relative to the codebase.","No mention of ADR, CLAUDE.md, or design-doc update for these architectural choices."],"finding":"The plan introduces novel architectural decisions (three-signal historical inference, inference-marker-present-only-when-true encoding, compaction/SNAPSHOT preservation contract) that are described in the ephemeral ticket body but are not explicitly committed to a persistent ADR, CLAUDE.md entry, or standalone design doc. Future maintainers inheriting the codebase without the ticket context may not find the reasoning for these choices.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa032eb01b1fc169d","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section; Scope/Decomposition sections; AC for docs/event-schema.md and docs/output-schemas.md","norm_id":"n418c4b797e859a64","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A future engineer adds a new reconciler and is unsure whether to add a fourth inference signal or extend the closed vocabulary — no canonical decision record explains the deliberate conservatism.","A maintainer debugging SNAPSHOT replay finds unexpected 'unknown' projections and has no persistent doc explaining why missing/None signals intentionally project unknown rather than inferring."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a docs/architecture/creation-channel-provenance.md (or an ADR entry) covering: (1) why only Jira legacy inference is supported and the exact three-signal predicate; (2) the 'const: true / key absent' marker convention and its trust-boundary semantics; (3) the compaction invariant (process_snapshot restores unknown compiled_state keys verbatim). Reference this doc from the updated event-schema.md.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify whether `ensure_identity_for` validates its `creation_channel` argument (or threads it opaquely to `create_identity_core`), and add an AC or test pin in story e622 that asserts placeholder identity creation via the Jira inbound path reports `jira` — not just that `inbound_recorded` tests pass for ticket creation.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Current `ensure_identity_for` (identity.py lines 327-380) has no `creation_channel` parameter; it calls `create_identity_core(...)` without one","Story 6fe2 AC: 'New local writers reject unknown or values outside the closed enum' — validation is at `create_core`, not at `ensure_identity_for`","Plan's risk mitigation says 'enumerate every create_core and direct CREATE writer call site and pin each public facade/helper with a behavioral test' but the `ensure_identity_for` channel threading is a multi-hop pass-through that could be missed"],"finding":"The plan specifies that `ensure_identity_for` will accept a `creation_channel` parameter (story 6fe2 adds it with a `python` default), but does not specify whether `ensure_identity_for` itself validates the channel value. If story e622 forgets to thread `creation_channel=\"jira\"` through the `_ensure_inbound_assignee_identity → rebar.ensure_identity_for` call, the placeholder identity is silently attributed to `python` rather than `jira` — with no rejection or warning because the default is valid.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7824b7b2feb011d0","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"e622 description: '_ensure_inbound_assignee_identity passes creation_channel=\"jira\" through rebar.ensure_identity_for -> identity.ensure_identity_for -> create_identity_core -> create_core. The dependency story owns these signatures with python defaults; this story owns only the Jira argument at the inbound boundary.'","norm_id":"n7c789350142759ce","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Story e622 implementer wires `creation_channel=\"jira\"` into `apply_inbound_records._ensure_inbound_assignee_identity` but forgets to thread it through `rebar.ensure_identity_for`; placeholder identities for inbound Jira assignees silently report `python` in audit output with no test failure unless a behavioral test for this exact path exists."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"insufficient","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The historical Jira inference predicate — the plan's sole novel behavioral rule — relies on exact string comparison of 'author equals reconciler' and 'env_id equals reconciler', but the plan never specifies what literal string value(s) constitute 'reconciler' for each field, nor does it reference the single source-of-truth location (inbound_translate._event_meta or equivalent). This makes the novel inference rule formally underspecified: an implementer who independently discovers the wrong constant will produce a predicate that silently never fires (or misfires on a rename), with no compile-time or schema-time guard.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f09b45f96d82a59ed","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Historical records without the field project jira only when all creation-stable signals agree: the ticket ID uses the reconciler-generated jira- prefix and the genesis/restored author and env_id are both reconciler.'","norm_id":"ne73318cd8dd625e9","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the Architecture Decisions section (and mirrored in child ticket e622's Approach Rationale), replace 'author and env_id are both reconciler' with the actual quoted constant(s) and add a reference like: 'The exact string is the value produced by inbound_translate._event_meta's author/env_id defaults — reference that constant directly rather than re-encoding it in the reducer helper.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify in Architecture Decisions (or the story e622 description) whether reconciler-created placeholder identities share the apply_inbound_records.py creation seam or require a separate channel declaration, and update the two-seam description in Context accordingly.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["AC2 text: 'Newly materialized Jira issues plus reconciler-created placeholder identities report jira'","Scope IN: 'All CREATE-backed helper flows, including ideas, identities, and session logs' — no mention of placeholder identities","Architecture Decisions: only 'Jira inbound creation composes CREATE data in apply_inbound_records.py' — no separate placeholder-identity path described","Context section: names the two creation seams as composer.py:create_core and apply_inbound_records.py — placeholder identity creation is not listed as a distinct seam"],"finding":"AC2 names 'reconciler-created placeholder identities' as a distinct entity type that must report jira, but the plan body (Architecture Decisions, Scope IN, Risks) refers only to 'identities' generically and says nothing about how or whether the Jira reconciler creates placeholder identities via a different code path from standard Jira inbound creation. Without a description of this pathway, implementers cannot determine whether it already converges on apply_inbound_records.py or requires separate instrumentation.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f68bf0382914d4a2f","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC2 ('reconciler-created placeholder identities report jira') vs Architecture Decisions and Scope IN","norm_id":"n362d43d2b6193e22","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer may not know whether placeholder identity creation goes through apply_inbound_records.py (already covered) or through a separate reconciler helper that needs its own channel declaration.","A test written for -k inbound_recorded may pass for standard Jira issues but miss a placeholder-identity code path that was never instrumented."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a paragraph to Architecture Decisions (and update Scope IN / story e622 description) specifying that outbound Jira binding/sync events must preserve — not overwrite — the stored creation_channel, naming the code location(s) involved and the invariant to enforce.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["AC3 text: 'Outbound Jira binding or synchronization preserves the existing local creation channel. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k outbound'","Scope IN lists 'Jira inbound' but not outbound sync","Architecture Decisions: no sentence addresses what happens to creation_channel during outbound Jira writes","Decomposition story e622: described only as 'Jira/import attribution and conservative legacy Jira inference'"],"finding":"AC3 ('Outbound Jira binding or synchronization preserves the existing local creation channel') is an orphan criterion: the plan body contains no description of what the outbound Jira pathway does with creation_channel. Architecture Decisions cover only inbound Jira creation and legacy inference; Scope IN lists only 'Jira inbound'; Decomposition story e622 is described as 'Jira/import attribution and conservative legacy Jira inference.' The outbound concern (that a later Jira sync event does not clobber or lose the stored channel) has no corresponding architectural decision, no named code location, and no risk mitigation entry, yet its test proves real implementation work.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fde012c6939060c0f","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC3 ('Outbound Jira binding or synchronization preserves the existing local creation channel') and Architecture Decisions / Scope IN","norm_id":"n1d95969a001f00a8","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer of story e622 has no spec guidance on whether outbound sync code should read-and-preserve, skip, or assert-no-change for creation_channel — they must guess, risking either a silent overwrite or a missing test.","A reviewer checking e622's scope will not find outbound Jira behavior in the plan, creating ambiguity about whether the AC belongs to e622 or to a later story."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In Architecture Decisions, add a bullet such as: 'Outbound Jira binding and synchronization events (e.g. JIRA_BIND, JIRA_SYNC) are not CREATE events and must never set or overwrite creation_channel; the compiled state projection ignores creation_channel on non-CREATE events. Apply-outbound code in [file] asserts no creation_channel key is present in the outgoing mutation.' Update Scope IN to read 'Jira inbound and outbound-sync channel preservation' and add the invariant to the Risks section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add or extend AC#2 (or a dedicated AC) to prove that reconciler-created ideas and session logs (if produced by the jira inbound path) also report the `jira` creation channel, closing the helper-coverage gap for the jira ingress path.","cohort":["E3","F4"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["'All CREATE-backed helper flows, including ideas, identities, and session logs, attributed to the interface that invoked them.'","AC#1: 'standard tickets, ideas, identities, plus session logs' — covers only cli/mcp/python","AC#2: 'reconciler-created placeholder identities report jira' — covers identities only, not ideas or session logs for the jira path"],"finding":"The Scope/IN clause promises 'All CREATE-backed helper flows, including ideas, identities, and session logs, attributed to the interface that invoked them,' but AC#2 only proves reconciler-created placeholder identities report jira — reconciler-created ideas or session logs (if any) have no explicit AC coverage, leaving 'every ingress path' for helpers partially unproven.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa0a1dcba740d2b94","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope > IN (helpers clause) vs. Acceptance Criteria #1 and #2","norm_id":"n2bda4de824afb545","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A reconciler flow that creates a linked idea or session log would not be covered by any AC, so the jira channel attribution for those helpers could silently regress."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Extend the AC#2 test file (tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py) with parametrized cases for any helper entity types (ideas, session logs) the reconciler can emit, verifying they report channel=jira just as placeholder identities do.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"insufficient","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"insufficient","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py' (full file, no -k filter) to e622 AC4's regression proof, or add a separate e622 AC that pins existing NDJSON export behavior unchanged.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Parent AC6 proof: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check'","e622 AC4 proof: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py -k creation_channel'","6fe2 scope OUT: 'NDJSON import' and export not listed; its AC6 does not include test_export_ndjson.py","568c file_impact does not include test_export_ndjson.py; no verify_command references it","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Parent AC6 requires the full test_export_ndjson.py suite to pass (no -k filter), but no child runs the file without a filter. Child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 covers only '-k creation_channel'; child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 does not touch that file at all; child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 does not list it. Any pre-existing or newly introduced regression in non-creation_channel NDJSON export tests would satisfy all child ACs yet fail the parent proof command.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f86a40df57ea69326","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74, AC4 (test_export_ndjson.py -k creation_channel) vs. parent AC6 (full test_export_ndjson.py run)","norm_id":"n1cd3f9564fcc5385","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An existing test in test_export_ndjson.py (e.g., for source_* field serialization or round-trip export fidelity) breaks when e622 changes import_ndjson.py or _provenance.py, but the -k filter silently passes the child AC while the parent metric fails.","A reviewer completes all three child stories and attempts to close the parent, only to find the unfiltered parent proof command fails on a non-creation_channel test."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 AC4, change the proof to run the full file: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py' and add a secondary regression assertion 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py' to the existing-behavior AC7.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"57d2a703076d419a","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":270.7,"llm_calls":22,"llm_ms":463990.9,"total_ms":464395.3,"verify_requests":1},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"jira-reb-977","ticket_type":"epic","verdict":"PASS","verified_at_sha":"cb0f8ec3b0641860ea6139431ccc63ca528c4732"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784261740258901001,"uuid":"ba1af2ee-753f-427e-9eee-8bd4ef078c3a"}